dc_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Odessa, sheet R-66. A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4375)
dc_description_s: Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4375. Alternate title: Odessa. Lambert conical orthomorphic projection. Danube zone grid. Gradient tints and isogonic data deleted by AMS, 1949. Relief shown by 50 and 100 meter contour intervals and and spot elevations. With Romanian and Russian glossaries. Corrected from intelligence reports up to Oct. 1944. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete. Geographic area on map is designated as Romania, it is now part of Moldova.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1949.
